WEBVTT

00:00:17.983 --> 00:00:19.527
What would have happened

00:00:19.568 --> 00:00:21.862
<i>if I had used my Fist of
Flowing Water, Crushed Rock...?</i>

00:00:22.571 --> 00:00:23.948
Saitama, huh?

00:00:24.573 --> 00:00:27.576
<i>It'd be a shame to just
leave him to his own devices.</i>

00:00:28.577 --> 00:00:33.082
THE EXCESSIVELY PUSHY BANG

00:00:35.417 --> 00:00:36.961
Maybe there's some way—

00:00:39.713 --> 00:00:40.965
<i>Hm? Genos?</i>

00:00:41.757 --> 00:00:43.008
<i>Why are they together?</i>

00:00:43.592 --> 00:00:45.177
<i>Come to think of it...</i>

00:00:45.970 --> 00:00:47.054
Master!

00:00:47.846 --> 00:00:50.599
Are they teacher and student?

00:00:51.475 --> 00:00:53.936
But their rankings are
Class S and Class C.

00:00:53.978 --> 00:00:55.354
So what's going on?

00:00:57.106 --> 00:00:58.899
What should we have for dinner?

00:00:59.525 --> 00:01:01.318
| think we've got some cabbage left.

00:01:01.485 --> 00:01:03.320
Cabbage alone will not be enough.

00:01:04.113 --> 00:01:05.698
Shall I purchase some meat?

00:01:06.115 --> 00:01:08.284
There you go again.

00:01:08.742 --> 00:01:11.370
Listen, don't underestimate cabbage!

00:01:11.745 --> 00:01:14.290
Stir-fried in yakiniku sauce,
it goes great with rice.

00:01:15.207 --> 00:01:18.919
<i>Hmm...so they are indeed
teacher and student.</i>

00:01:19.086 --> 00:01:22.631
| see. So preparation is what
truly dictates the results.

00:01:23.090 --> 00:01:26.302
Even a powerful weapon can be junk
in the hands of the incompetent.

00:01:27.219 --> 00:01:29.096
Is that the lesson, Master?

00:01:29.680 --> 00:01:31.515
| wouldn't go that far.

00:01:31.640 --> 00:01:33.183
You teach me so much, Master!

00:01:34.351 --> 00:01:35.352
Incredible!

00:01:35.811 --> 00:01:39.523
<i>He preaches the principles of
martial arts with leftover cabbage!</i>

00:01:40.149 --> 00:01:44.194
And a disciple so quick fo pick up
on his master's lessons...

00:01:44.361 --> 00:01:46.280
Such a far cry from Charanko.

00:01:50.993 --> 00:01:52.328
If I don't do something,

00:01:52.369 --> 00:01:54.872
the Fist of Flowing Water,
Crushed Rock ends with me.

00:01:55.414 --> 00:01:56.332
All right.

00:01:57.666 --> 00:02:02.338
Aw man! All your talk about meat
made me hungry for some!

00:02:02.504 --> 00:02:03.380
Hello!

00:02:04.340 --> 00:02:05.549
Quite impressive.

00:02:06.175 --> 00:02:07.676
Who's this old guy again?

00:02:08.177 --> 00:02:09.261
Silverfang.

00:02:09.845 --> 00:02:11.639
The Class S hero, Master.

00:02:11.889 --> 00:02:13.390
Just call me Bang.

00:02:14.683 --> 00:02:17.811
Up close, he appears to be
no more than an ordinary guy.

00:02:18.729 --> 00:02:21.106
Genos looks superior
in every respect.

00:02:21.190 --> 00:02:23.359
<i>Yet, Saitama is the one guiding him.</i>

00:02:23.525 --> 00:02:27.529
In terms of rank,
Genos is placed much higher.

00:02:28.364 --> 00:02:30.532
But if Saitama has mastered
a fighting style

00:02:30.574 --> 00:02:33.077
that can surpass rankings,
it's a different story.

00:02:33.744 --> 00:02:36.538
What's with the old guy?
He's gone all quiet...

00:02:36.747 --> 00:02:39.249
There are many eccentrics in Class S.

00:02:39.416 --> 00:02:43.337
<i>I suppose that means this Saitama
is an outstanding teacher.</i>

00:02:44.588 --> 00:02:46.090
— Ready?
—Yes.

00:02:47.508 --> 00:02:48.926
So Saitama...

00:02:49.718 --> 00:02:51.428
do you have a teacher?

00:02:51.470 --> 00:02:51.970
Huh?

00:02:52.388 --> 00:02:55.683
Where did you learn martial arts?
Which style do you practice?

00:02:56.100 --> 00:02:58.936
So we go from silence to
a barrage of questions?

00:02:59.269 --> 00:03:02.231
Even if your style isn't mainstream,
don't be embarrassed—

00:03:02.272 --> 00:03:03.857
Nah, I don't have a teacher.

00:03:04.108 --> 00:03:06.944
But then.. how did you
become so strong?

00:03:07.403 --> 00:03:10.280
Um...weight lifting...| guess?

00:03:10.364 --> 00:03:11.240
What!

00:03:11.365 --> 00:03:13.200
So you're saying that
you smashed that meteor

00:03:13.242 --> 00:03:14.702
using pure physical ability?

00:03:15.119 --> 00:03:16.203
Yeah, sure.

00:03:16.537 --> 00:03:19.081
This kid has so much potential!

00:03:20.874 --> 00:03:23.961
How about stopping by
my dojo one day?

00:03:24.128 --> 00:03:25.796
It might be interesting.

00:03:25.879 --> 00:03:27.214
No, I'm good.

00:03:27.256 --> 00:03:29.341
Master Saitama is a busy man.

00:03:29.508 --> 00:03:31.385
Come on, don't be like that.

00:03:32.136 --> 00:03:34.263
This is the address for my dojo.

00:03:34.304 --> 00:03:35.848
I'll be there all day tomorrow.

00:03:35.973 --> 00:03:37.433
Were you listening?

00:03:37.474 --> 00:03:38.976
— Master is—
— All right, old man.

00:03:39.476 --> 00:03:40.310
See you tomorrow.

00:03:40.477 --> 00:03:41.812
Oh, Master!

00:03:44.523 --> 00:03:48.068
<i>| can't wait to see their faces
lit with enthusiasm.</i>

00:04:00.414 --> 00:04:02.124
Why hasn't he come?!

00:04:04.877 --> 00:04:07.713
| thought for sure you were
going to the dojo.

00:04:07.963 --> 00:04:11.133
Yeah, old dudes like that
can be persistent.

00:04:11.508 --> 00:04:13.552
Humoring them,
then blowing them off

00:04:13.594 --> 00:04:15.345
is the only way
to avoid big headaches.

00:04:17.723 --> 00:04:19.349
Not a care in the world.

00:04:20.309 --> 00:04:22.728
But one should never
let his guard down.

00:04:23.979 --> 00:04:24.813
You're wide open!

00:04:26.190 --> 00:04:30.027
I could've defeated him 200 times
while he was shopping.

00:04:30.152 --> 00:04:33.697
<i>He's so very vulnerable
and inexperienced.</i>

00:04:39.161 --> 00:04:40.162
Master!

00:04:44.917 --> 00:04:48.045
| thought it was a cat,
but it was just a plastic bag.

00:04:48.754 --> 00:04:50.506
And now all my delicious meat

00:04:50.631 --> 00:04:53.050
has been run over by a truck...

00:04:53.550 --> 00:04:55.385
Such physical prowess!

00:04:55.511 --> 00:04:58.222
<i>No wonder he walks around
So open to attack.</i>

00:04:58.347 --> 00:05:01.391
This changes all of
my mental simulations.

00:05:02.518 --> 00:05:04.895
You two look like
you're in need of some protein.

00:05:07.189 --> 00:05:08.732
At my dojo,

00:05:08.774 --> 00:05:12.569
| have some premium meat that
the Martial Arts Association sent over.

00:05:13.612 --> 00:05:14.988
That's quite a coincidence.

00:05:15.030 --> 00:05:17.407
| happen to have
some yakiniku sauce!

00:05:17.741 --> 00:05:19.576
Where's your dojo?

00:05:20.202 --> 00:05:21.537
ADVANCE FEARLESSLY
TOWARDS ONE'S GOAL

00:05:21.537 --> 00:05:22.120
ADVANCE FEARLESSLY TOWARDS ONE'S GOAL But, before I give
you the meat, there's something I'd like you to see.

00:05:22.120 --> 00:05:25.749
But, before I give you the meat,
there's something I'd like you to see.

00:05:32.214 --> 00:05:33.215
What do you think?

00:05:33.298 --> 00:05:35.342
| was hoping I could open your eyes
to how marvelous

00:05:35.384 --> 00:05:36.510
the martial arts are—

00:05:37.052 --> 00:05:39.346
Yeah, I get it.
Now hurry up and give us the meat.

00:05:39.596 --> 00:05:41.807
What is it that you want?

00:05:42.474 --> 00:05:46.645
<i>Looks like I'll have to
make them understand...</i>

00:05:47.062 --> 00:05:48.647
— But if I fight them,
— We were promised meat.

00:05:48.730 --> 00:05:50.315
— There's a possibility
— Why are we breaking bricks?

00:05:50.399 --> 00:05:52.442
— They may get hurt. All right...
— Ahh, this is becoming a pain.

