KARUTA FOR
GOOD BOYS AND GIRLS

00:05:53.235 --> 00:05:54.862
KARUTA FOR GOOD BOYS AND
GIRLS Let's have a game of karuta!

00:05:54.862 --> 00:05:54.945
KARUTA FOR
GOOD BOYS AND GIRLS

00:05:55.153 --> 00:05:57.447
Hey, what about the meat?

00:05:57.573 --> 00:05:59.616
Win the game and it's yours.

00:06:00.534 --> 00:06:02.327
Charanko, you read the cards.

00:06:02.452 --> 00:06:03.412
Yes, sir!

00:06:08.417 --> 00:06:09.543
Nu...

00:06:10.294 --> 00:06:11.503
What the—!

00:06:12.713 --> 00:06:13.630
How's that?

00:06:13.672 --> 00:06:15.716
By sharpening every nerve
in my body,

00:06:15.757 --> 00:06:17.759
| can react instantaneously.

00:06:17.926 --> 00:06:20.220
That is the essence of martial arts.

00:06:23.640 --> 00:06:24.474
Ro...

00:06:27.936 --> 00:06:28.979
Got it.

00:06:29.104 --> 00:06:33.650
| see. The one who can flick
more cards wins.

00:06:34.192 --> 00:06:35.819
All right. Hurry up and
read the next one.

00:06:35.944 --> 00:06:38.822
Wait a moment!
You can't neglect the rules.

00:06:39.489 --> 00:06:43.327
These guys aren't the type to
quietly play games inside.

00:06:44.453 --> 00:06:45.621
Apparently so.

00:06:46.204 --> 00:06:47.122
In that case...

00:06:48.415 --> 00:06:52.044
This is an old training method
passed down in our dojo.

00:06:52.294 --> 00:06:54.504
It's a kind of freestyle sparring.

00:06:54.671 --> 00:06:56.423
First, the two players must decide

00:06:56.465 --> 00:06:58.592
who will attack and
who will defend.

00:06:58.675 --> 00:07:03.263
This is decided via
shitao, jiandao and—

00:07:03.305 --> 00:07:04.348
You mean "rock-paper-scissors."

00:07:05.807 --> 00:07:07.643
The winner then has the right to

00:07:07.684 --> 00:07:10.062
pick up the weapon and
hit the other guy.

00:07:10.187 --> 00:07:12.773
Hit, cover, rock-paper-scissors, right?

00:07:13.023 --> 00:07:15.859
Yeah, generally that's the idea...

00:07:16.026 --> 00:07:18.654
But in a competition such as this,
martial arts can work

00:07:18.695 --> 00:07:19.947
to your advantage—

00:07:19.988 --> 00:07:21.907
Master, I'll do it.

00:07:22.157 --> 00:07:23.867
You understand the rules?

00:07:23.951 --> 00:07:26.161
Yes. I figured the explanation
would take forever,

00:07:26.203 --> 00:07:27.537
so I looked them up myself.

00:07:28.038 --> 00:07:29.748
Very well.

00:07:29.831 --> 00:07:31.333
ROUND ONE

00:07:31.667 --> 00:07:34.211
— Hit! Cover! Rock, paper, scissors!
— Hit! Cover! Rock, paper, scissors!

00:07:40.425 --> 00:07:41.969
First blood.

00:07:42.344 --> 00:07:44.179
Still just a rookie, eh?

00:07:45.347 --> 00:07:48.225
Maybe this is too advanced
for you kids?

00:07:49.017 --> 00:07:50.727
Looks like fun.

00:07:51.061 --> 00:07:52.854
Tag out, Genos!

00:07:53.021 --> 00:07:55.232
ROUND TWO

00:07:55.232 --> 00:07:56.191
ROUND TWO — Hit! Cover! Rock, paper,
scissors! — Hit! Cover! Rock, paper, scissors!

00:07:56.191 --> 00:07:57.818
— Hit! Cover! Rock, paper, scissors!
— Hit! Cover! Rock, paper, scissors!

00:08:04.783 --> 00:08:06.910
Damn. Let's go again!

00:08:07.577 --> 00:08:08.787
Fine.

00:08:08.870 --> 00:08:09.454
ROUND THREE

00:08:09.454 --> 00:08:10.414
ROUND THREE — Rock, paper,
scissors! — Rock, paper, scissors!

00:08:10.414 --> 00:08:10.914
— Rock, paper, scissors!
— Rock, paper, scissors!

